esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when Kubernetes nodes report out of disk status.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Node out_of_disk=true — no disk space remaining, node unschedulable.
//
// Common causes:
// Log accumulation, large images, temporary files, insufficient disk provisioning.
//
// Action needed:
// Clean up disk, expand volume, remove unused images and containers.
//
// To scope to a cluster, add: AND `orchestrator.cluster.name` == "YOUR_CLUSTER"
TS metrics-kubernetes.node-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.node.status.out_of_disk` == "true"
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.node.name`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
